00:00:09.144 --> 00:00:27.482 align:middle line:90%


00:00:27.482 --> 00:00:29.690 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: We're
all familiar with the notion

00:00:29.690 --> 00:00:32.049 align:middle line:10%
that we've been
manipulated as a society.

00:00:32.049 --> 00:00:34.070 align:middle line:10%
Eldon Taylor's new
book, "Gotcha,"

00:00:34.070 --> 00:00:35.960 align:middle line:10%
attempts to help you
find yourself amidst

00:00:35.960 --> 00:00:38.965 align:middle line:10%
the misinformation by peeling
back all that you are not,

00:00:38.965 --> 00:00:41.090 align:middle line:10%
and I think that was the
term in the book-- peeling

00:00:41.090 --> 00:00:42.585 align:middle line:10%
back all that you are not.

00:00:42.585 --> 00:00:43.460 align:middle line:90%
>>ELDON TAYLOR: True.

00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:45.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you know,
first of all, let's start

00:00:45.540 --> 00:00:46.790 align:middle line:90%
with the foreword of the book.

00:00:46.790 --> 00:00:50.330 align:middle line:84%
Your wife is saying, you've
been spending all this time

00:00:50.330 --> 00:00:52.190 align:middle line:84%
in self-help for
all these years.

00:00:52.190 --> 00:00:55.329 align:middle line:84%
What made you go the
direction of conspiracy?

00:00:55.329 --> 00:00:57.870 align:middle line:10%
>>TAYLOR: You know, and I don't
consider it to be conspiracy,

00:00:57.870 --> 00:01:01.530 align:middle line:10%
so I would correct that some.

00:01:01.530 --> 00:01:04.160 align:middle line:10%
There's a lot of talk
about tinfoil hats,

00:01:04.160 --> 00:01:09.920 align:middle line:10%
and that's itself a
manipulation mechanism.

00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:12.080 align:middle line:90%
Let me give you a case in point.

00:01:12.080 --> 00:01:17.120 align:middle line:84%
We have officials from
the CIA and the NSA,

00:01:17.120 --> 00:01:19.670 align:middle line:84%
and they testified before
Congress that they would never

00:01:19.670 --> 00:01:23.380 align:middle line:90%
use or spy upon Americans.

00:01:23.380 --> 00:01:28.530 align:middle line:84%
Then Snowden comes out, and we
discovered, no, they both lied,

00:01:28.530 --> 00:01:30.557 align:middle line:84%
that, indeed, that's
exactly what they're doing.

00:01:30.557 --> 00:01:31.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Of course, yeah.

00:01:31.640 --> 00:01:34.220 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: We
recently had Vault7,

00:01:34.220 --> 00:01:36.200 align:middle line:84%
and we discovered
that the CIA has

00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:42.260 align:middle line:84%
all sorts of devices
they can use to spy

00:01:42.260 --> 00:01:43.850 align:middle line:90%
on everything that we do.

00:01:43.850 --> 00:01:47.270 align:middle line:84%
Your Samsung television
is watching you.

00:01:47.270 --> 00:01:50.330 align:middle line:84%
Your smartphone is
following everything you do,

00:01:50.330 --> 00:01:53.750 align:middle line:90%
picking up all your email.

00:01:53.750 --> 00:01:55.740 align:middle line:84%
They can remote control
your automobile.

00:01:55.740 --> 00:01:56.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:01:56.540 --> 00:01:57.650 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: OK?

00:01:57.650 --> 00:02:00.890 align:middle line:84%
Well, when you look at
that, is that a conspiracy

00:02:00.890 --> 00:02:04.904 align:middle line:84%
theory, or was that a factual
statement that was made--

00:02:04.904 --> 00:02:06.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with you--

00:02:06.070 --> 00:02:08.470 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: That it took
us time to catch up to--

00:02:08.470 --> 00:02:09.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Embrace.

00:02:09.270 --> 00:02:09.710 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: Right.

00:02:09.710 --> 00:02:12.001 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean there was
a saying that I really like.

00:02:12.001 --> 00:02:14.840 align:middle line:84%
It said "a better term
for conspiracy theory

00:02:14.840 --> 00:02:17.340 align:middle line:84%
is unspeakable truths,"
and I happen to like that.

00:02:17.340 --> 00:02:18.140 align:middle line:90%
That's my favorite.

00:02:18.140 --> 00:02:18.500 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: I agree.

00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:19.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We know they're true.

00:02:19.610 --> 00:02:21.320 align:middle line:84%
I'm just kind of
throwing it, and maybe I

00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:23.840 align:middle line:84%
should choose my
words more carefully.

00:02:23.840 --> 00:02:26.460 align:middle line:84%
Conspiracy theory--
no, it's not.

00:02:26.460 --> 00:02:28.160 align:middle line:84%
These unspeakable
truths-- what made

00:02:28.160 --> 00:02:31.460 align:middle line:84%
you turn to an interest in
these unspeakable truths?

00:02:31.460 --> 00:02:32.930 align:middle line:84%
And you need to
know also-- and I'm

00:02:32.930 --> 00:02:36.032 align:middle line:84%
sure you do-- my audience is
aware of virtually all of them,

00:02:36.032 --> 00:02:38.240 align:middle line:84%
and I've done in-depth
interviews on almost every one

00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:39.350 align:middle line:90%
of them already.

00:02:39.350 --> 00:02:41.900 align:middle line:84%
And so they're familiar
with that body of knowledge.

00:02:41.900 --> 00:02:45.770 align:middle line:84%
What made you turn to
that body of knowledge?

00:02:45.770 --> 00:02:48.410 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: I don't
see it as a turn.

00:02:48.410 --> 00:02:52.580 align:middle line:84%
What I see is I've spent my
career trying to understand

00:02:52.580 --> 00:02:55.270 align:middle line:90%
why people do what people do.

00:02:55.270 --> 00:02:58.910 align:middle line:84%
As you know, I was a practicing
criminalist for many years,

00:02:58.910 --> 00:03:03.080 align:middle line:84%
so my typical day was made up
of running lie detection tests

00:03:03.080 --> 00:03:07.010 align:middle line:84%
or conducting a forensic
hypnosis session

00:03:07.010 --> 00:03:10.760 align:middle line:90%
or supervising an investigation.

00:03:10.760 --> 00:03:16.610 align:middle line:84%
And I would repeatedly hear
people use rationalizations

00:03:16.610 --> 00:03:19.670 align:middle line:84%
as to why they did
what they did that just

00:03:19.670 --> 00:03:21.660 align:middle line:90%
didn't make any real sense.

00:03:21.660 --> 00:03:23.450 align:middle line:90%
I remember one case.

00:03:23.450 --> 00:03:24.710 align:middle line:90%
This was a young fellow.

00:03:24.710 --> 00:03:28.430 align:middle line:84%
He was tall, good-looking, from
a good family, had everything

00:03:28.430 --> 00:03:31.740 align:middle line:84%
in the world going for him,
had a very pretty wife.

00:03:31.740 --> 00:03:34.610 align:middle line:84%
They had a baby that
was due to come,

00:03:34.610 --> 00:03:38.210 align:middle line:84%
and he decided that it
was his fatherly role

00:03:38.210 --> 00:03:41.690 align:middle line:84%
to fix a nursery
up for the child.

00:03:41.690 --> 00:03:43.670 align:middle line:84%
So he stole lumber
from his employer.

00:03:43.670 --> 00:03:46.610 align:middle line:84%
I picked him up in a
lie detection test.

00:03:46.610 --> 00:03:48.320 align:middle line:84%
We ultimately got
the confession,

00:03:48.320 --> 00:03:50.750 align:middle line:84%
and I heard this story
that, well, you know,

00:03:50.750 --> 00:03:54.050 align:middle line:84%
the home that we're living
in doesn't have a nursery.

00:03:54.050 --> 00:03:56.360 align:middle line:84%
It's not large enough, so
I went into the basement,

00:03:56.360 --> 00:03:58.670 align:middle line:84%
and I stole this
lumber, so I could

00:03:58.670 --> 00:04:00.320 align:middle line:90%
build a nursery for my child.

00:04:00.320 --> 00:04:04.310 align:middle line:84%
I just felt that I owed that
to my wife and my unborn child.

00:04:04.310 --> 00:04:07.010 align:middle line:84%
Now where I can
sympathize and even

00:04:07.010 --> 00:04:11.150 align:middle line:84%
empathize with that
rationalization,

00:04:11.150 --> 00:04:12.900 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't make any real sense.

00:04:12.900 --> 00:04:15.470 align:middle line:90%
The man gave up his life.

00:04:15.470 --> 00:04:16.880 align:middle line:90%
He became a felon.

00:04:16.880 --> 00:04:19.550 align:middle line:90%
He lost his right to vote.

00:04:19.550 --> 00:04:24.170 align:middle line:84%
Think of the impact of that
decision, that process.

00:04:24.170 --> 00:04:27.020 align:middle line:84%
What makes people
do what they do?

00:04:27.020 --> 00:04:29.840 align:middle line:84%
To me, self-help is
about understanding

00:04:29.840 --> 00:04:36.050 align:middle line:84%
who we are, becoming authentic
about how we live, what

00:04:36.050 --> 00:04:39.340 align:middle line:90%
we believe, why we believe it.

00:04:39.340 --> 00:04:43.130 align:middle line:84%
And it became clear to me
over the years of research,

00:04:43.130 --> 00:04:44.930 align:middle line:90%
more than approaching--

00:04:44.930 --> 00:04:46.790 align:middle line:84%
I'm dating myself
now-- but approaching

00:04:46.790 --> 00:04:50.180 align:middle line:84%
40 years of research,
it became clear to me

00:04:50.180 --> 00:04:53.720 align:middle line:84%
that people didn't understand
that for all intent

00:04:53.720 --> 00:04:57.320 align:middle line:84%
and purposes, it's our
subconscious mind that's

00:04:57.320 --> 00:05:00.920 align:middle line:84%
motivating, that's priming
everything they do.

00:05:00.920 --> 00:05:04.670 align:middle line:84%
In fact, today we
take FMRI studies,

00:05:04.670 --> 00:05:07.470 align:middle line:90%
and we watch the brain lifetime.

00:05:07.470 --> 00:05:13.280 align:middle line:84%
And if I were to
give you a problem,

00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:17.420 align:middle line:84%
let's say the problem,
Regina, was a paragraph long.

00:05:17.420 --> 00:05:19.820 align:middle line:84%
And I gave you a button for
your right hand and a button

00:05:19.820 --> 00:05:23.330 align:middle line:84%
for your left hand to indicate
A or B or true or false,

00:05:23.330 --> 00:05:25.656 align:middle line:84%
depending on the
nature of the question.

00:05:25.656 --> 00:05:31.110 align:middle line:84%
An MRI technician watching you
make your decision on average

00:05:31.110 --> 00:05:36.230 align:middle line:84%
will know six seconds before you
do what you're going to decide.

00:05:36.230 --> 00:05:39.990 align:middle line:84%
That ought to cause everyone
great pause right there.

00:05:39.990 --> 00:05:43.230 align:middle line:84%
Six seconds before you know
what you're going to do,

00:05:43.230 --> 00:05:46.140 align:middle line:84%
a technician watching
your brain will know

00:05:46.140 --> 00:05:47.450 align:middle line:90%
what you're going to choose.

00:05:47.450 --> 00:05:47.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That
actually makes sense.

00:05:47.820 --> 00:05:50.100 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: Which button
you're going to push.

00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:53.610 align:middle line:84%
So it becomes incumbent
upon each of us

00:05:53.610 --> 00:05:56.550 align:middle line:84%
to explore what's in
our own unconscious.

00:05:56.550 --> 00:06:00.030 align:middle line:10%
I mean, the fact of the
matter is Benjamin Libet,

00:06:00.030 --> 00:06:06.050 align:middle line:10%
years ago, utilizing
multi-cranial EEG, witnessed

00:06:06.050 --> 00:06:10.800 align:middle line:10%
the so-called P300 wave, the
cortical evoked response,

00:06:10.800 --> 00:06:15.340 align:middle line:10%
occurring in areas of the
brain known to be unconscious

00:06:15.340 --> 00:06:19.440 align:middle line:10%
and theorized that before
there is any conscious action,

00:06:19.440 --> 00:06:21.720 align:middle line:10%
we get this P300
wave that indicates

00:06:21.720 --> 00:06:25.290 align:middle line:10%
we have action out of the
unconscious predisposing that.

00:06:25.290 --> 00:06:29.670 align:middle line:84%
Well, FMRI studies,
as I said, clearly

00:06:29.670 --> 00:06:32.460 align:middle line:84%
demonstrate that
to be the truth.

00:06:32.460 --> 00:06:35.070 align:middle line:84%
But the work of Libet started
this whole conversation

00:06:35.070 --> 00:06:36.810 align:middle line:90%
about free will.

00:06:36.810 --> 00:06:39.320 align:middle line:84%
If what's going
on, if what we do,

00:06:39.320 --> 00:06:43.470 align:middle line:84%
if what we believe, if what
we think, if all of that,

00:06:43.470 --> 00:06:47.160 align:middle line:84%
including our motor
movements, occurs initially

00:06:47.160 --> 00:06:50.250 align:middle line:84%
in the unconscious,
what is free will?

00:06:50.250 --> 00:06:51.870 align:middle line:90%
Do we have free will?

00:06:51.870 --> 00:06:54.910 align:middle line:84%
Well, most scientists
today would say no.

00:06:54.910 --> 00:06:56.169 align:middle line:90%
It's a grand illusion.

00:06:56.169 --> 00:06:58.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They would if they're
looking at it from a material

00:06:58.710 --> 00:07:00.084 align:middle line:84%
science point of
view, of course,

00:07:00.084 --> 00:07:02.150 align:middle line:84%
but not if you're
looking beyond that.

00:07:02.150 --> 00:07:03.090 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: Well, I'm not
going to disagree with that.

00:07:03.090 --> 00:07:04.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It makes
perfect sense.

00:07:04.170 --> 00:07:04.710 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: But--

00:07:04.710 --> 00:07:06.918 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you can't look
at the brain and the way

00:07:06.918 --> 00:07:09.090 align:middle line:84%
the mind works from a
materialistic point of view,

00:07:09.090 --> 00:07:11.040 align:middle line:84%
from a scientific
materialism point of view.

00:07:11.040 --> 00:07:12.060 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't work.

00:07:12.060 --> 00:07:14.393 align:middle line:84%
That's why all the conundrums,
why they don't understand

00:07:14.393 --> 00:07:16.290 align:middle line:90%
anything about the brain yet.

00:07:16.290 --> 00:07:20.100 align:middle line:84%
If they understood it more as
a processing unit for a larger

00:07:20.100 --> 00:07:23.330 align:middle line:84%
body that is feeding it, then
you have something different

00:07:23.330 --> 00:07:25.260 align:middle line:90%
called the subconscious mind.

00:07:25.260 --> 00:07:26.540 align:middle line:90%
You can't map it.

00:07:26.540 --> 00:07:27.340 align:middle line:90%
They can't map it.

00:07:27.340 --> 00:07:30.090 align:middle line:84%
There's no material way to
map the way the whole mind is

00:07:30.090 --> 00:07:33.060 align:middle line:84%
actually working
through the brain.

00:07:33.060 --> 00:07:35.190 align:middle line:84%
I think that's the big
problem, which, of course,

00:07:35.190 --> 00:07:35.900 align:middle line:90%
there would be a delay.

00:07:35.900 --> 00:07:38.050 align:middle line:84%
You could see a brain center
light up, for example,

00:07:38.050 --> 00:07:39.257 align:middle line:90%
in advance of a response.

00:07:39.257 --> 00:07:41.340 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: See, now I don't
disagree that the brain

00:07:41.340 --> 00:07:42.542 align:middle line:90%
is the ultimate frontier.

00:07:42.542 --> 00:07:43.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No, it's not.

00:07:43.500 --> 00:07:45.810 align:middle line:90%
The mind is, but not the brain.

00:07:45.810 --> 00:07:48.600 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: I do agree that mind
is greater than the brain.

00:07:48.600 --> 00:07:52.730 align:middle line:84%
We have action of
mind at a distance.

00:07:52.730 --> 00:07:54.490 align:middle line:84%
We know that such
a thing occurs.

00:07:54.490 --> 00:07:56.365 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, Dean
Radin's work and so forth.

00:07:56.365 --> 00:07:58.060 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: Yeah, all right.

00:07:58.060 --> 00:07:59.960 align:middle line:90%
Dean Radin is a good example.

00:07:59.960 --> 00:08:01.900 align:middle line:84%
You can take a simple
thing like remove

00:08:01.900 --> 00:08:06.430 align:middle line:84%
some of the glial cells from
your mouth, put part of them

00:08:06.430 --> 00:08:10.180 align:middle line:84%
in a Petri dish, take part
of them five miles away,

00:08:10.180 --> 00:08:12.727 align:middle line:84%
shock the Petri dish,
and at the same moment,

00:08:12.727 --> 00:08:13.935 align:middle line:90%
you'll see those [INAUDIBLE].

00:08:13.935 --> 00:08:15.025 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Spooky
action at a distance.

00:08:15.025 --> 00:08:15.825 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:08:15.825 --> 00:08:18.020 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: So we know
that there is actually--

00:08:18.020 --> 00:08:19.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Mind is
not in the brain.

00:08:19.500 --> 00:08:20.300 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:08:20.300 --> 00:08:21.379 align:middle line:90%
It's a processing unit.

00:08:21.379 --> 00:08:23.920 align:middle line:84%
I think once the science starts
looking at it as a processing

00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:25.720 align:middle line:84%
unit, all their
questions are not

00:08:25.720 --> 00:08:27.330 align:middle line:84%
going to be
mysteries any longer.

00:08:27.330 --> 00:08:29.580 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: But let's deal
with it as a processing unit.

00:08:29.580 --> 00:08:30.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:08:30.380 --> 00:08:33.130 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: The processing
unit itself, for all intent

00:08:33.130 --> 00:08:35.679 align:middle line:90%
and purposes, has limitations.

00:08:35.679 --> 00:08:40.274 align:middle line:84%
Those limitations include
what Freud would call

00:08:40.274 --> 00:08:43.419 align:middle line:90%
our id, our ego, our super ego.

00:08:43.419 --> 00:08:46.720 align:middle line:84%
They would include
a Thanatos drive.

00:08:46.720 --> 00:08:49.180 align:middle line:84%
We're not free of
being an animal.

00:08:49.180 --> 00:08:51.395 align:middle line:90%
All those reptilian signals--

00:08:51.395 --> 00:08:52.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's very true.

00:08:52.520 --> 00:08:54.670 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: --systems,
they still exist.

00:08:54.670 --> 00:08:58.360 align:middle line:84%
We sometimes deny
our physiology.

00:08:58.360 --> 00:09:00.610 align:middle line:90%
You could take your right foot.

00:09:00.610 --> 00:09:01.810 align:middle line:90%
Do it right now.

00:09:01.810 --> 00:09:05.140 align:middle line:84%
Pick it up, and move it
in a clockwise circle.

00:09:05.140 --> 00:09:07.080 align:middle line:90%
And then write six in the air.

00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:09.500 align:middle line:84%
Then discover that,
wait a minute.

00:09:09.500 --> 00:09:12.910 align:middle line:84%
My foot doesn't remain
going in a clockwise signal.

00:09:12.910 --> 00:09:15.430 align:middle line:84%
I could sit you
down and give you

00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:17.350 align:middle line:84%
something to do
with your right hand

00:09:17.350 --> 00:09:20.660 align:middle line:84%
while you answered or
responded to stimulus

00:09:20.660 --> 00:09:23.020 align:middle line:90%
I was giving you very rapidly.

00:09:23.020 --> 00:09:27.310 align:middle line:84%
And the whole notion here
would be, identify that signal

00:09:27.310 --> 00:09:28.480 align:middle line:90%
every time you see it.

00:09:28.480 --> 00:09:31.780 align:middle line:84%
And if I put something
in your right hand, which

00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:34.210 align:middle line:84%
is connected to your
left brain, you'll

00:09:34.210 --> 00:09:37.720 align:middle line:84%
identify it far more
times accurately

00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:40.920 align:middle line:84%
than if I gave you something
to do with your left hand.

00:09:40.920 --> 00:09:43.300 align:middle line:84%
You'll fail to
notice it many times.

00:09:43.300 --> 00:09:46.545 align:middle line:84%
So there are some very
real physiological limits--

00:09:46.545 --> 00:09:47.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:48.690 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: --to how we
process information.

00:09:48.690 --> 00:09:50.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And the
reptilian brain

00:09:50.050 --> 00:09:51.300 align:middle line:90%
still works with our survival.

00:09:51.300 --> 00:09:54.700 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: So if we look
at processing information,

