00:19:19.094 --> 00:19:20.260 align:middle line:90%
the worst thing we could do.

00:19:20.260 --> 00:19:23.680 align:middle line:84%
Little Johnny is told in
kindergarten, oh, Johnny,

00:19:23.680 --> 00:19:25.390 align:middle line:90%
you shouldn't get angry.

00:19:25.390 --> 00:19:27.010 align:middle line:90%
Anger is not good for you.

00:19:27.010 --> 00:19:28.570 align:middle line:90%
Anger is bad.

00:19:28.570 --> 00:19:30.340 align:middle line:90%
Johnny, angry, you just--

00:19:30.340 --> 00:19:34.210 align:middle line:84%
anger is something that
you never want to have.

00:19:34.210 --> 00:19:37.780 align:middle line:84%
So little Johnny, to use
Robert Bly's words in his book,

00:19:37.780 --> 00:19:41.560 align:middle line:84%
"The Dark Side of
our Shadow," puts it

00:19:41.560 --> 00:19:44.552 align:middle line:90%
in this imaginary long bag.

00:19:44.552 --> 00:19:45.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You stuff it.

00:19:45.510 --> 00:19:46.635 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: And so he takes--

00:19:46.635 --> 00:19:48.250 align:middle line:84%
you know, we take
all these emotions

00:19:48.250 --> 00:19:51.430 align:middle line:84%
that we have that we're
not supposed to have,

00:19:51.430 --> 00:19:53.650 align:middle line:84%
all these thoughts that
we have that we're not

00:19:53.650 --> 00:19:56.140 align:middle line:84%
supposed to have, and we
stick them in this long bag.

00:19:56.140 --> 00:19:57.910 align:middle line:84%
But we're dragging
them along with us.

00:19:57.910 --> 00:19:59.000 align:middle line:90%
We're never healing them.

00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:00.249 align:middle line:90%
We're never dealing with them.

00:20:00.249 --> 00:20:01.690 align:middle line:90%
We're never facing them.

00:20:01.690 --> 00:20:04.330 align:middle line:84%
We don't even want to
recognize they exist.

00:20:04.330 --> 00:20:07.090 align:middle line:84%
And then one day,
we blow up maybe

00:20:07.090 --> 00:20:09.000 align:middle line:84%
at our wife for no
reason, but there

00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:12.460 align:middle line:84%
have been stimuli throughout
the day that has us on edge,

00:20:12.460 --> 00:20:14.650 align:middle line:90%
and boom, we dump it out.

00:20:14.650 --> 00:20:18.250 align:middle line:84%
OK, what we should
be doing is looking

00:20:18.250 --> 00:20:23.050 align:middle line:84%
at each of these thoughts
and not in a judgmental way.

00:20:23.050 --> 00:20:26.860 align:middle line:84%
So I have the thought,
where did that come from?

00:20:26.860 --> 00:20:29.140 align:middle line:90%
Why would I think that?

00:20:29.140 --> 00:20:32.920 align:middle line:84%
When was the first time I
had a thought like that?

00:20:32.920 --> 00:20:36.610 align:middle line:84%
Is there-- is that a
thought I want to own,

00:20:36.610 --> 00:20:40.540 align:middle line:84%
is there another context
I can think about this in?

00:20:40.540 --> 00:20:42.310 align:middle line:90%
Context is everything.

00:20:42.310 --> 00:20:45.040 align:middle line:84%
It takes somebody either
in 5 o'clock traffic,

00:20:45.040 --> 00:20:47.150 align:middle line:84%
and you're in a
hurry to get home.

00:20:47.150 --> 00:20:48.760 align:middle line:84%
You've got tickets
to the theater.

00:20:48.760 --> 00:20:51.380 align:middle line:84%
Your wife or husband
is waiting for you.

00:20:51.380 --> 00:20:53.590 align:middle line:84%
You were late in the
office, and suddenly a car

00:20:53.590 --> 00:20:55.330 align:middle line:90%
cuts in front of you.

00:20:55.330 --> 00:20:57.810 align:middle line:90%
The natural reaction is what?

00:20:57.810 --> 00:20:59.890 align:middle line:90%
The middle finger?

00:20:59.890 --> 00:21:01.570 align:middle line:90%
Lay on the horn?

00:21:01.570 --> 00:21:06.580 align:middle line:84%
Adrenaline, cortisol, neither of
which are good for the optimal

00:21:06.580 --> 00:21:10.130 align:middle line:84%
operation of your immune,
endochrine, or [? ANS. ? ]

00:21:10.130 --> 00:21:14.700 align:middle line:84%
So how could I change that
context, so the next time

00:21:14.700 --> 00:21:17.590 align:middle line:84%
it happened to me, I
wouldn't respond that way?

00:21:17.590 --> 00:21:19.470 align:middle line:84%
Well, what if I
just begin to think

00:21:19.470 --> 00:21:21.990 align:middle line:84%
that if a car cuts
in front of me,

00:21:21.990 --> 00:21:24.150 align:middle line:84%
maybe they have a
small child laying

00:21:24.150 --> 00:21:27.900 align:middle line:84%
on the floorboards in the
back seat that's bleeding,

00:21:27.900 --> 00:21:30.360 align:middle line:90%
and they need emergency medical?

00:21:30.360 --> 00:21:32.790 align:middle line:84%
If I change that
context, suddenly, I

00:21:32.790 --> 00:21:34.830 align:middle line:84%
don't mind that they
got in front of me.

00:21:34.830 --> 00:21:38.080 align:middle line:84%
I'm blessing them that they
get on down the highway.

00:21:38.080 --> 00:21:39.600 align:middle line:90%
We choose the context.

00:21:39.600 --> 00:21:43.440 align:middle line:84%
We can volitionally choose
to change the context

00:21:43.440 --> 00:21:46.290 align:middle line:84%
and reframe all of
these so-called--

00:21:46.290 --> 00:21:49.950 align:middle line:84%
and in that process, we
begin to make uncoverings.

00:21:49.950 --> 00:21:54.160 align:middle line:84%
So we discover a
young man can't laugh.

00:21:54.160 --> 00:21:56.370 align:middle line:90%
He's in his late 30s.

00:21:56.370 --> 00:21:58.200 align:middle line:90%
He's considered a stoic.

00:21:58.200 --> 00:22:00.030 align:middle line:90%
He's not invited to any parties.

00:22:00.030 --> 00:22:03.840 align:middle line:84%
It's bearing hard on his
relationship with his wife.

00:22:03.840 --> 00:22:06.720 align:middle line:90%
They seek marriage counseling.

00:22:06.720 --> 00:22:08.880 align:middle line:84%
In the counseling
and uncovering,

00:22:08.880 --> 00:22:12.270 align:middle line:84%
a hypnotic
uncovering, revivifies

00:22:12.270 --> 00:22:18.540 align:middle line:84%
when he had his first
negative reaction to laughter.

00:22:18.540 --> 00:22:20.460 align:middle line:90%
And he's a small boy.

00:22:20.460 --> 00:22:22.200 align:middle line:90%
He's seven, eight years old.

00:22:22.200 --> 00:22:26.820 align:middle line:84%
He's with a group of kids, and
somebody tells a story that's

00:22:26.820 --> 00:22:28.920 align:middle line:90%
funny, and he laughs.

00:22:28.920 --> 00:22:30.780 align:middle line:90%
Tears come down his face.

00:22:30.780 --> 00:22:32.580 align:middle line:90%
He doubles over.

00:22:32.580 --> 00:22:35.490 align:middle line:84%
He smiles a little funny
because of a partial paralysis

00:22:35.490 --> 00:22:36.290 align:middle line:90%
on his face.

00:22:36.290 --> 00:22:38.490 align:middle line:90%
They make fun of his face.

00:22:38.490 --> 00:22:42.340 align:middle line:84%
They ridicule and criticize
him, and a defense mechanism.

00:22:42.340 --> 00:22:43.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:22:43.140 --> 00:22:44.900 align:middle line:84%
This is how the
subconscious works, yes.

00:22:44.900 --> 00:22:47.010 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: And so now
that defense mechanism

00:22:47.010 --> 00:22:49.380 align:middle line:84%
says, we'll never
be ridiculed again.

00:22:49.380 --> 00:22:50.660 align:middle line:90%
So we won't laugh.

00:22:50.660 --> 00:22:51.460 align:middle line:90%
We won't smile.

00:22:51.460 --> 00:22:54.060 align:middle line:84%
He finds many things
funny, but because

00:22:54.060 --> 00:22:58.080 align:middle line:84%
of that adaptation
at a very young age,

00:22:58.080 --> 00:23:02.760 align:middle line:84%
it changes his entire life,
impacts his friendships,

00:23:02.760 --> 00:23:05.580 align:middle line:90%
his family, etc.

00:23:05.580 --> 00:23:09.710 align:middle line:84%
These mechanisms are all
a part of who we are,

00:23:09.710 --> 00:23:12.060 align:middle line:84%
and in order to
flesh them out, we

00:23:12.060 --> 00:23:14.330 align:middle line:84%
need to get into
our own unconscious,

00:23:14.330 --> 00:23:17.880 align:middle line:84%
our own subconscious, and
discover what they are.

00:23:17.880 --> 00:23:20.220 align:middle line:84%
Hypnosis is a tool,
as you know, that

00:23:20.220 --> 00:23:24.150 align:middle line:84%
can be very beneficial in
that process in uncovering,

00:23:24.150 --> 00:23:27.150 align:middle line:84%
but just being mindful,
paying attention

00:23:27.150 --> 00:23:30.810 align:middle line:84%
to every single thought
we have, and then,

00:23:30.810 --> 00:23:34.710 align:middle line:84%
as I say, without
discriminating, without judging

00:23:34.710 --> 00:23:38.220 align:middle line:84%
that thought, simply
accepting that that was ours,

00:23:38.220 --> 00:23:42.100 align:middle line:84%
owning it, and then the healing
it, whatever it might be,

00:23:42.100 --> 00:23:44.350 align:middle line:90%
or changing its context.

00:23:44.350 --> 00:23:47.910 align:middle line:84%
That's a first step to any
sense of self-actualization.

00:23:47.910 --> 00:23:49.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:23:49.590 --> 00:23:52.500 align:middle line:90%
Meditation 101, be mindful.

00:23:52.500 --> 00:23:54.330 align:middle line:90%
Pay attention to your thoughts.

00:23:54.330 --> 00:23:57.600 align:middle line:84%
Most people don't accomplish any
of those things in the reality

00:23:57.600 --> 00:23:59.090 align:middle line:90%
day to day in their lives.

00:23:59.090 --> 00:24:01.200 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: They've been
trained to be consumers.

00:24:01.200 --> 00:24:04.320 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And also, life
is zinging in so quickly

00:24:04.320 --> 00:24:06.450 align:middle line:84%
that there is not
enough time, even,

00:24:06.450 --> 00:24:09.580 align:middle line:84%
in most people's perception
to respond to anything.

00:24:09.580 --> 00:24:11.054 align:middle line:90%
You're multitasking.

00:24:11.054 --> 00:24:12.720 align:middle line:84%
Which of those things
are you taking in?

00:24:12.720 --> 00:24:13.890 align:middle line:84%
Which ones do you
stop and think,

00:24:13.890 --> 00:24:16.140 align:middle line:84%
why am I doing this, this,
and this at this moment?

00:24:16.140 --> 00:24:18.760 align:middle line:84%
So yes, I think mindfulness
is a great idea.

00:24:18.760 --> 00:24:20.826 align:middle line:84%
I mean absolutely, we
should all be mindful.

00:24:20.826 --> 00:24:22.200 align:middle line:84%
If you meditate,
I think it makes

00:24:22.200 --> 00:24:24.280 align:middle line:84%
it a little easier for
people to be slowed

00:24:24.280 --> 00:24:28.200 align:middle line:84%
down enough to be mindful,
for example, in your driving

00:24:28.200 --> 00:24:29.240 align:middle line:90%
example.

00:24:29.240 --> 00:24:30.882 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: Meditation is key.

00:24:30.882 --> 00:24:32.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
meditation is really key.

00:24:32.590 --> 00:24:35.070 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: We know that
you can change your brain.

00:24:35.070 --> 00:24:36.630 align:middle line:84%
You can increase
your gray matter.

00:24:36.630 --> 00:24:39.360 align:middle line:90%
You can rewire your brain.

00:24:39.360 --> 00:24:44.870 align:middle line:84%
Indeed, you can influence
the manifestation of the DNA.

00:24:44.870 --> 00:24:46.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Right, we
can do all of that.

00:24:46.660 --> 00:24:49.830 align:middle line:84%
So again, I'm trying to get
back to all of these events

00:24:49.830 --> 00:24:52.960 align:middle line:84%
you're writing about and where
you're taking people with it.

00:24:52.960 --> 00:24:55.181 align:middle line:90%
Is it to show them, again--

00:24:55.181 --> 00:24:56.430 align:middle line:90%
because I want to progress it.

00:24:56.430 --> 00:24:58.920 align:middle line:90%
We know we've been hoodwinked.

00:24:58.920 --> 00:25:01.410 align:middle line:84%
We know that we're under
mass hypnosis, essentially,

00:25:01.410 --> 00:25:03.060 align:middle line:90%
all the time.

00:25:03.060 --> 00:25:07.590 align:middle line:84%
And so coming from
that point of view,

00:25:07.590 --> 00:25:10.230 align:middle line:84%
let's talk about the
pragmatic ways in which we

00:25:10.230 --> 00:25:12.630 align:middle line:90%
can break the hypnotic trance.

00:25:12.630 --> 00:25:15.420 align:middle line:84%
Again, most people's
subconscious--

00:25:15.420 --> 00:25:18.240 align:middle line:84%
I mean this goes back, some
would argue, for lifetimes, not

00:25:18.240 --> 00:25:20.790 align:middle line:84%
just even this lifetime,
what's carried around

00:25:20.790 --> 00:25:22.200 align:middle line:90%
in the subconscious.

00:25:22.200 --> 00:25:25.380 align:middle line:84%
And it is subbed our
ability to recognize.

00:25:25.380 --> 00:25:27.780 align:middle line:84%
So unless you do something
like deep meditation

00:25:27.780 --> 00:25:30.150 align:middle line:84%
with an eye toward this,
or unless you do hypnosis,

00:25:30.150 --> 00:25:34.640 align:middle line:84%
for example, the possibility of
actually uncovering everything

00:25:34.640 --> 00:25:37.590 align:middle line:84%
or a significant amount of it
what's in the subconscious,

00:25:37.590 --> 00:25:39.940 align:middle line:84%
that, in itself, would
be a lifetime endeavor,

00:25:39.940 --> 00:25:41.150 align:middle line:90%
if you just did that.

