00:47:18.940 --> 00:47:21.970 align:middle line:84%
say is the unique
opportunity to a nation that

00:47:21.970 --> 00:47:28.750 align:middle line:84%
is in shock, traumatized,
jubilant, divided,

00:47:28.750 --> 00:47:32.070 align:middle line:84%
moving into deep
patterns of hatred?

00:47:32.070 --> 00:47:34.230 align:middle line:84%
What is the unique
opportunity for those

00:47:34.230 --> 00:47:38.430 align:middle line:84%
who exploit among a population
like this in this state of mind

00:47:38.430 --> 00:47:39.495 align:middle line:90%
right now?

00:47:39.495 --> 00:47:42.030 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: See now therein
comes the question that

00:47:42.030 --> 00:47:44.250 align:middle line:84%
is among my favorite,
and it leads

00:47:44.250 --> 00:47:48.960 align:middle line:84%
back to what you said about
why "Gotcha," if all your work

00:47:48.960 --> 00:47:51.240 align:middle line:90%
has been about self-help?

00:47:51.240 --> 00:47:53.890 align:middle line:84%
Spirituality is
what our lives are

00:47:53.890 --> 00:47:55.140 align:middle line:90%
about as far as I'm concerned.

00:47:55.140 --> 00:47:56.865 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Your background
was also as a pastor.

00:47:56.865 --> 00:47:57.906 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: That's correct.

00:47:57.906 --> 00:48:00.787 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean you have a
deep interest, in your case,

00:48:00.787 --> 00:48:01.745 align:middle line:90%
Christian spirituality.

00:48:01.745 --> 00:48:03.440 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: I'm a
certified diplomat.

00:48:03.440 --> 00:48:04.972 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Right,
spirituality, yeah.

00:48:04.972 --> 00:48:05.930 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: That's right.

00:48:05.930 --> 00:48:11.090 align:middle line:84%
So the bottom line
comes down to this.

00:48:11.090 --> 00:48:14.750 align:middle line:84%
If we're spiritual beings,
as we claim most of us

00:48:14.750 --> 00:48:19.310 align:middle line:84%
that we are, how can
all this animus, all

00:48:19.310 --> 00:48:25.740 align:middle line:84%
this froth of anger,
hate, including deceit,

00:48:25.740 --> 00:48:29.440 align:middle line:84%
how can we continue to
participate in that?

00:48:29.440 --> 00:48:34.390 align:middle line:84%
So what we have right now is a
trauma, and trauma, you know,

00:48:34.390 --> 00:48:37.510 align:middle line:84%
has this remarkable
healing power.

00:48:37.510 --> 00:48:39.770 align:middle line:84%
Trauma tends to send
us back to our roots.

00:48:39.770 --> 00:48:40.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It does.

00:48:40.570 --> 00:48:43.630 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: Trauma tends to
make us stop for a minute

00:48:43.630 --> 00:48:45.350 align:middle line:90%
and view what's important.

00:48:45.350 --> 00:48:48.270 align:middle line:84%
What's the most important
thing in our lives?

00:48:48.270 --> 00:48:52.090 align:middle line:84%
With the division that we
have in the world today,

00:48:52.090 --> 00:48:54.250 align:middle line:84%
we have the
opportunity to, instead

00:48:54.250 --> 00:49:02.220 align:middle line:84%
of continue calling who's
right and who's wrong, to heal.

00:49:02.220 --> 00:49:05.330 align:middle line:84%
But we can't do that
without a broader picture.

00:49:05.330 --> 00:49:11.530 align:middle line:84%
We have to get out of this
notion that one side won,

00:49:11.530 --> 00:49:14.780 align:middle line:84%
and another side lost, and
one side wants to do this,

00:49:14.780 --> 00:49:16.770 align:middle line:84%
and the other side
wants to do that.

00:49:16.770 --> 00:49:20.450 align:middle line:84%
We have to get out of that, and
we have to stop and look at,

00:49:20.450 --> 00:49:28.740 align:middle line:84%
this is one people, one world,
one god, one spiritual system.

00:49:28.740 --> 00:49:31.760 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter what
you believe, as long

00:49:31.760 --> 00:49:37.820 align:middle line:84%
as what you do is your very best
to serve your fellow mankind.

00:49:37.820 --> 00:49:39.710 align:middle line:90%
I sit at the top.

00:49:39.710 --> 00:49:42.860 align:middle line:90%
We're hardwired for giving.

00:49:42.860 --> 00:49:45.770 align:middle line:84%
I have a four-cornered
philosophy about life

00:49:45.770 --> 00:49:48.080 align:middle line:90%
that I spell out very simply.

00:49:48.080 --> 00:49:51.650 align:middle line:84%
It's based on 40
years of research,

00:49:51.650 --> 00:49:57.290 align:middle line:84%
but that fourth corner
is called service.

00:49:57.290 --> 00:50:00.380 align:middle line:84%
Years ago, I had a
woman come to my offices

00:50:00.380 --> 00:50:03.520 align:middle line:84%
in Las Vegas, Nevada, had been
referred by a psychiatrist,

00:50:03.520 --> 00:50:05.840 align:middle line:90%
and she was suicidal.

00:50:05.840 --> 00:50:09.800 align:middle line:84%
Self-flagellation was a
regular thing with her.

00:50:09.800 --> 00:50:13.306 align:middle line:84%
She was on all kinds of
drugs, and it'd basically

00:50:13.306 --> 00:50:14.930 align:middle line:84%
come to a point where
they weren't sure

00:50:14.930 --> 00:50:16.100 align:middle line:90%
what they could do.

00:50:16.100 --> 00:50:19.370 align:middle line:84%
So she came to me for
pastoral counseling.

00:50:19.370 --> 00:50:22.490 align:middle line:84%
When I looked at her intake
sheets, the first thing I saw

00:50:22.490 --> 00:50:26.990 align:middle line:84%
was that her first therapist
was Milton Erickson.

00:50:26.990 --> 00:50:28.640 align:middle line:90%
You know who Milton Erickson is.

00:50:28.640 --> 00:50:30.680 align:middle line:90%
To me, he walks on water.

00:50:30.680 --> 00:50:33.630 align:middle line:84%
So I honestly had one of these
moments, where I thought,

00:50:33.630 --> 00:50:36.260 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what I could
do or what I would--

00:50:36.260 --> 00:50:39.300 align:middle line:84%
I mean I don't know why
I would see this person.

00:50:39.300 --> 00:50:43.990 align:middle line:84%
If he, Milton Erickson, couldn't
help her, what would I do?

00:50:43.990 --> 00:50:47.020 align:middle line:84%
But you know sometimes
in those moments,

00:50:47.020 --> 00:50:49.160 align:middle line:90%
we receive inspiration.

00:50:49.160 --> 00:50:52.700 align:middle line:84%
And I believe I
received inspiration.

00:50:52.700 --> 00:50:54.880 align:middle line:84%
So I agreed to see
her in what's called

00:50:54.880 --> 00:50:58.120 align:middle line:84%
brief therapy, 10 sessions,
once a week for 10 weeks.

00:50:58.120 --> 00:51:01.420 align:middle line:84%
Now this was a
suicidal individual,

00:51:01.420 --> 00:51:03.250 align:middle line:90%
but we had to have a contract.

00:51:03.250 --> 00:51:06.740 align:middle line:84%
She had to have homework, and
she had to do the homework,

00:51:06.740 --> 00:51:09.400 align:middle line:84%
or I'd just stop seeing her,
period, end of quotation.

00:51:09.400 --> 00:51:11.590 align:middle line:90%
But it was simple homework.

00:51:11.590 --> 00:51:16.510 align:middle line:84%
She was to obtain a journal, and
the first day that first week,

00:51:16.510 --> 00:51:21.240 align:middle line:84%
she was to do one good
deed every single day.

00:51:21.240 --> 00:51:23.740 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the day, she was
to write that good deed down.

00:51:23.740 --> 00:51:27.850 align:middle line:84%
Now this good deed had to be
for somebody she didn't know,

00:51:27.850 --> 00:51:31.840 align:middle line:84%
so this had to be for a stranger
or maybe for a fellow employee

00:51:31.840 --> 00:51:34.300 align:middle line:90%
that she didn't really like.

00:51:34.300 --> 00:51:38.400 align:middle line:84%
So you had to go out of your
way to do the good deed.

00:51:38.400 --> 00:51:41.440 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of the
night when she'd retire,

00:51:41.440 --> 00:51:44.050 align:middle line:84%
she were to write that
down in her journal,

00:51:44.050 --> 00:51:47.530 align:middle line:84%
what the good deed was, how
she thought it made that person

00:51:47.530 --> 00:51:50.710 align:middle line:90%
feel, and how it made her feel.

00:51:50.710 --> 00:51:51.970 align:middle line:90%
Week two, it was two.

00:51:51.970 --> 00:51:53.230 align:middle line:90%
Week three, it was three.

00:51:53.230 --> 00:51:54.190 align:middle line:90%
Week four, it was four.

00:51:54.190 --> 00:51:56.580 align:middle line:90%
We got up to five.

00:51:56.580 --> 00:51:58.840 align:middle line:84%
And you know, to begin with,
some of these good deeds

00:51:58.840 --> 00:52:01.150 align:middle line:90%
were pretty paltry.

00:52:01.150 --> 00:52:04.510 align:middle line:84%
But by the time 10
weeks were over,

00:52:04.510 --> 00:52:08.170 align:middle line:84%
she was off a lot of her drugs
and was no longer suicidal,

00:52:08.170 --> 00:52:11.790 align:middle line:84%
because self-esteem
isn't something

00:52:11.790 --> 00:52:14.860 align:middle line:84%
I get from the number
of degrees I've earned

00:52:14.860 --> 00:52:20.500 align:middle line:84%
or the awards I've won, the
trophies, the property I own,

00:52:20.500 --> 00:52:22.240 align:middle line:90%
the car I drive.

00:52:22.240 --> 00:52:26.250 align:middle line:84%
Self-esteem is something
I get from what I give.

00:52:26.250 --> 00:52:28.050 align:middle line:90%
She was lacking self-esteem.

00:52:28.050 --> 00:52:30.360 align:middle line:84%
She didn't feel she
was worth living.

00:52:30.360 --> 00:52:33.570 align:middle line:84%
She had a real set
of circumstances,

00:52:33.570 --> 00:52:36.810 align:middle line:84%
where her sister
had died, and she

00:52:36.810 --> 00:52:40.240 align:middle line:84%
felt that it was she
who should have died.

00:52:40.240 --> 00:52:44.680 align:middle line:84%
And I won't go into the detail,
but she had real circumstances.

00:52:44.680 --> 00:52:47.250 align:middle line:84%
But what she learned over
the course of this time

00:52:47.250 --> 00:52:49.620 align:middle line:84%
is that her life
made a difference,

00:52:49.620 --> 00:52:54.570 align:middle line:84%
and in that process, she
began to build self-esteem.

00:52:54.570 --> 00:52:58.440 align:middle line:84%
She began to realize
that life did have value.

00:52:58.440 --> 00:53:01.470 align:middle line:84%
All right, we're faced
with an opportunity here.

00:53:01.470 --> 00:53:05.700 align:middle line:84%
Each of us can continue to feed
the narrative that is negative,

00:53:05.700 --> 00:53:09.570 align:middle line:84%
or we can begin to feed a
service-oriented negative.

00:53:09.570 --> 00:53:11.107 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what's
going to happen.

00:53:11.107 --> 00:53:11.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Narrative.

00:53:11.940 --> 00:53:14.610 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: I don't know
what Trump's going to do.

00:53:14.610 --> 00:53:16.620 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it will be
good for the country.

00:53:16.620 --> 00:53:18.390 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it won't be
good for the country.

00:53:18.390 --> 00:53:21.060 align:middle line:84%
But what is
absolutely devastating

00:53:21.060 --> 00:53:23.890 align:middle line:90%
the country is the division.

00:53:23.890 --> 00:53:28.800 align:middle line:84%
So it's time to step up and
start healing that division.

00:53:28.800 --> 00:53:31.080 align:middle line:84%
It's time to remind us
of what's important.

00:53:31.080 --> 00:53:34.650 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to tell you that
I've had the great opportunity

00:53:34.650 --> 00:53:39.690 align:middle line:84%
of dealing with elite athletes,
Hall of Fame athletes,

00:53:39.690 --> 00:53:43.690 align:middle line:84%
Fortune 500 executives
in my lifetime.

00:53:43.690 --> 00:53:47.220 align:middle line:84%
And they will all attest
to you that if what

00:53:47.220 --> 00:53:51.480 align:middle line:84%
you do in your life is about
service-- you're a plumber,

00:53:51.480 --> 00:53:52.800 align:middle line:90%
and you go to somebody's home.

00:53:52.800 --> 00:53:55.260 align:middle line:84%
And you ended up going there
just to collect your money

00:53:55.260 --> 00:53:58.320 align:middle line:84%
and fix a leaky faucet and
get on to the next house.

00:53:58.320 --> 00:54:00.870 align:middle line:84%
You can't wait until
lunchtime, but you're

00:54:00.870 --> 00:54:06.360 align:middle line:84%
going there to solve a
problem, to help this person.

00:54:06.360 --> 00:54:08.130 align:middle line:84%
If that's your
attitude, doesn't matter

00:54:08.130 --> 00:54:09.550 align:middle line:90%
what you do for a living--

00:54:09.550 --> 00:54:15.210 align:middle line:84%
plumber, electrician,
attorney, radio, TV host--

00:54:15.210 --> 00:54:19.170 align:middle line:84%
if that's your attitude,
you're there to help,

00:54:19.170 --> 00:54:23.200 align:middle line:84%
then your business will
prosper, and you will prosper,

00:54:23.200 --> 00:54:25.450 align:middle line:84%
because when you put your
head on the pillow at night,

00:54:25.450 --> 00:54:29.640 align:middle line:84%
you'll get this warm fuzzy
feeling, that feeling that

00:54:29.640 --> 00:54:32.680 align:middle line:84%
says, my life does
make a difference.

00:54:32.680 --> 00:54:34.240 align:middle line:84%
I was able to help
someone today.

00:54:34.240 --> 00:54:35.810 align:middle line:84%
I was able to go
to the aid of them,

00:54:35.810 --> 00:54:38.500 align:middle line:84%
and you are just
hardwired to then

00:54:38.500 --> 00:54:43.953 align:middle line:84%
be bathed with those wonderful
neurochemicals, the endorphins,

00:54:43.953 --> 00:54:46.055 align:middle line:90%
and you will feel better.

00:54:46.055 --> 00:54:47.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with you.

00:54:47.180 --> 00:54:49.459 align:middle line:84%
I think that was
brilliant strategy

00:54:49.459 --> 00:54:51.250 align:middle line:84%
that you used to work
with it, because it's

00:54:51.250 --> 00:54:52.825 align:middle line:90%
so simple but so true.

00:54:52.825 --> 00:54:55.450 align:middle line:84%
And I think of everything we've
talked about in this interview,

00:54:55.450 --> 00:54:57.130 align:middle line:84%
the most important
thing is exactly

00:54:57.130 --> 00:54:58.720 align:middle line:90%
that, what you've just said.

00:54:58.720 --> 00:55:02.080 align:middle line:84%
If we can find a way
to calm down the noise

00:55:02.080 --> 00:55:05.800 align:middle line:84%
and in our own way, offer
something of ourselves

00:55:05.800 --> 00:55:09.400 align:middle line:84%
into the world that we think
has some value to others,

00:55:09.400 --> 00:55:10.390 align:middle line:90%
then you're right.

00:55:10.390 --> 00:55:14.140 align:middle line:84%
That starts acting as a salve
and creating connective tissue

00:55:14.140 --> 00:55:15.580 align:middle line:90%
between people again.

00:55:15.580 --> 00:55:18.610 align:middle line:84%
I think that's very true,
because we've really--

00:55:18.610 --> 00:55:23.500 align:middle line:84%
that connective tissue has
been like totally broken down.

00:55:23.500 --> 00:55:27.707 align:middle line:84%
And so in your book,
really, I think

00:55:27.707 --> 00:55:30.040 align:middle line:84%
that's really what you're
working toward in that book is

00:55:30.040 --> 00:55:31.770 align:middle line:90%
this one thing.

00:55:31.770 --> 00:55:34.090 align:middle line:84%
You don't say it
in there, but how

00:55:34.090 --> 00:55:35.752 align:middle line:84%
do we build this
connective tissue?

00:55:35.752 --> 00:55:37.210 align:middle line:84%
And I only brought
it up, because I

00:55:37.210 --> 00:55:39.940 align:middle line:84%
think we do have a unique
situation being presented

00:55:39.940 --> 00:55:43.690 align:middle line:84%
to us as a culture right
now that could continue

00:55:43.690 --> 00:55:47.440 align:middle line:84%
to be traumatized by the
media in this divisiveness,

00:55:47.440 --> 00:55:49.430 align:middle line:84%
or it can-- and I
call it unplugged.

00:55:49.430 --> 00:55:51.260 align:middle line:84%
There are other
ways to get news--

00:55:51.260 --> 00:55:55.810 align:middle line:84%
unplug, and as you say, start
being of service to another.

00:55:55.810 --> 00:55:58.200 align:middle line:90%
Start employing classic virtues.

00:55:58.200 --> 00:55:59.950 align:middle line:90%
Start telling the truth.

00:55:59.950 --> 00:56:01.075 align:middle line:90%
That would be a good place.

00:56:01.075 --> 00:56:01.950 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: Absolutely.

00:56:01.950 --> 00:56:04.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Don't let these
politicians be our guide.

00:56:04.180 --> 00:56:06.370 align:middle line:84%
Start telling the truth
through each other.

00:56:06.370 --> 00:56:09.970 align:middle line:84%
So is that kind of-- is
that more what you're really

00:56:09.970 --> 00:56:11.320 align:middle line:90%
working toward in your book?

00:56:11.320 --> 00:56:13.410 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: And I think the
conclusion of "Gotcha,"

00:56:13.410 --> 00:56:16.120 align:middle line:84%
I hope people get
that out of it--

00:56:16.120 --> 00:56:19.480 align:middle line:84%
obviously, I didn't tell this
very particular story in there,

00:56:19.480 --> 00:56:25.120 align:middle line:84%
but the bottom line is
the most important thing

00:56:25.120 --> 00:56:29.390 align:middle line:84%
we can do with our own
lives is contribute.

00:56:29.390 --> 00:56:30.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree.

00:56:30.190 --> 00:56:31.773 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: There is
no way in the world

00:56:31.773 --> 00:56:38.250 align:middle line:84%
we can go off in our closet or
in church once, twice a week

00:56:38.250 --> 00:56:42.340 align:middle line:84%
or how many times we pray
a day, be spiritual people

00:56:42.340 --> 00:56:44.320 align:middle line:90%
and be disengaged.

00:56:44.320 --> 00:56:49.770 align:middle line:10%
We need to be engaged, and
we need to help one another.

00:56:49.770 --> 00:56:53.550 align:middle line:10%
And to do that, we really
need to be informed and become

00:56:53.550 --> 00:56:54.350 align:middle line:10%
authentic.

00:56:54.350 --> 00:56:56.350 align:middle line:10%
Remember who we really are.

00:56:56.350 --> 00:56:57.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree.

00:56:57.610 --> 00:57:00.040 align:middle line:84%
I agree with you, and it's
a good note to end on,

00:57:00.040 --> 00:57:03.077 align:middle line:84%
and I think it's a lovely
sentiment to leave people with.

00:57:03.077 --> 00:57:03.910 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: Wonderful.

00:57:03.910 --> 00:57:04.870 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much.

00:57:04.870 --> 00:57:06.790 align:middle line:84%
I've appreciated the
opportunity to share.

00:57:06.790 --> 00:57:08.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Thank you, Eldon.

00:57:08.200 --> 00:57:11.290 align:middle line:10%
Again, the title of the book
is, "Gotcha: The Subordination

00:57:11.290 --> 00:57:12.160 align:middle line:10%
of Free Will."

00:57:12.160 --> 00:57:15.910 align:middle line:10%
Until next time, thank you for
joining us here on Open Minds.

